    <text id="B1164T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Johnson's statement of June 1865 attests to the seizure of Wholey's property and
                    lumber by the military.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1865-06-15">
                            <abbr expan="June 15, 1865">June 15/65</abbr>
                        </date>
                        <name type="place"><abbr expan="Provost Marshall">Pro Mar</abbr>
                            Office<lb/>Staunton <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute/>
                </opener>

                <p>Personally appeared before me Thos S. Johnson <abbr expan="Captain">Capt</abbr>
                    &amp; <abbr expan="Provost Marshall">Pro Mar</abbr>, who after being duly
                    sworn deposeth and saith that on or about the last of April, the military
                    authorities seized and used a lot of Boards &amp; Plank belonging to Thomas
                    Wholey. Said Boards &amp; Plank were inside the <orig reg="barracks"
                        >barricks</orig>, the <abbr expan="amount">amt</abbr> taken is estimated at
                    twenty two Hundred feet (2200 feet)</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Sworn to and subscribed before me this (15th) day June 1865<lb/>Thos S.
                            Johnson<lb/><abbr expan="Captain">Capt</abbr> &amp; <abbr
                            expan="Provost">Pro</abbr> Marshall</salute>
                    <signed>Patrick Hassete</signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">Mr Wholey has the bill of lumber for which he paid <orig
                            reg="$2.50">$2 50/100</orig> per (100) feet<lb/>[signed]Thos S. Johnson,
                            <abbr expan="Captain">Capt</abbr> &amp; <abbr
                            expan="Provost Marshall">Pro Mar</abbr></seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
